img { width: max/min(250px, 25vw); }

> : child combinator selector used between seletors to target only elements that match the second selector and are a direct child of the first selector 
nav > ul {
  display: flex; 
  justify-content: space-evenly; 
}

role attribute : indivate purpose behind an element on the page
  - aria-labelledby attribute used to reference region

sr-only : text only a screen reader can read 
common patter used to visually hide tet for only screen readers to read : 
.sr-only {
  position: absolute;
  width: 1px;
  height: 1px;
  padding: 0;
  margin: -1px;
  overflow: hidden;
  clip: rect(0, 0, 0, 0);
  white-space: nowrap;
  border: 0;
}

address commonly included in footer
- <br /> lets each text be on it's own line 
- dot not have to contain physical geogrpahical locaiton, can be used to provide a link to the subject 
  <address>
    freeCodeCamp<br />
    San Francisco<br />
    California<br />
    USA
  </address>

Contast betwen text and bakground of a heading should be at least 4.5:1

list-style property to control what bullets in list look like 

accesskey attribuet accepts a space-separated list of acess keys, keyboard shortcut on google : alt + accesskey
